name: Body Slam
battleEffect: The user drops onto the target with its full body weight. This may also leave the target with paralysis.
secondaryEffect: May induce paralysis.

name: Night Daze
battleEffect: The user lets loose a pitch-black shock wave at its target. This may also lower the target's accuracy.
secondaryEffect: May lower opponent's Accuracy one stage.

name: Conversion
battleEffect: The user changes its type to become the same type as the move at the top of the list of moves it knows.
secondaryEffect: User changes type into an own move's type.

name: Thief
battleEffect: The user attacks and steals the target's held item simultaneously. The user can't steal anything if it already holds an item.
secondaryEffect: May steal opponent's item (temporarily in trainer battles).

name: Punishment
battleEffect: The more the target has powered up with stat changes, the greater the move's power.
secondaryEffect: Increases damage inflicted based on the opponent's stat boosts

name: Skill Swap
battleEffect: The user employs its psychic power to exchange Abilities with the target.
secondaryEffect: User and target trade abilities.

name: Inferno
battleEffect: The user attacks by engulfing the target in an intense fire. This leaves the target with a burn.
secondaryEffect: May induce burn.

name: Phantom Force
battleEffect: The user vanishes somewhere, then strikes the target on the next turn. This move hits even if the target protects itself.
secondaryEffect: The user is protected the first turn, Attacks the second turn. Hits through Protect

name: Snore
battleEffect: This attack can be used only if the user is asleep. The harsh noise may also make the target flinch.
secondaryEffect: Can only be used while asleep.

name: Foresight
battleEffect: Enables a Ghost-type target to be hit by Normal- and Fighting-type attacks. This also enables an evasive target to be hit.
secondaryEffect: Allows opponent to be hit if Evasion is high. Allows Ghost-type Pokémon to be hit by Normal-type moves.
zMoveUgradeEffectDetailed: Increases Critical Hit Ratio by 2 stages

name: Clear Smog
battleEffect: The user attacks by throwing a clump of special mud. All stat changes are returned to normal.
secondaryEffect: Removes all stat changes

name: Knock Off
battleEffect: The user slaps down the target's held item, and that item can't be used in that battle. The move does more damage if the target has a held item.
secondaryEffect: Knocks down opponent's held item to prevent its use. Increases power by 50% if so.

name: Fire Fang
battleEffect: The user bites with flame-cloaked fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it with a burn.
secondaryEffect: May BURN opponent or cause opponent to flinch.

name: Power-Up Punch
battleEffect: Striking opponents over and over makes the user's fists harder. Hitting a target raises the Attack stat.
secondaryEffect: Raises user's Attack by one stage

name: Lunar Dance
battleEffect: The user faints. In return, the Pokémon taking its place will have its status and HP fully restored.
secondaryEffect: Causes the user to faint and completely heals the next Pokémon

name: Baton Pass
battleEffect: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting and passes along any stat changes.
secondaryEffect: Switches out the user but stat changes remain.

name: Sand Attack
battleEffect: Sand is hurled in the target's face, reducing the target's accuracy.
secondaryEffect: Lowers opponent's Accuracy one stage.

name: Seismic Toss
battleEffect: The target is thrown using the power of gravity. It inflicts damage equal to the user's level.
secondaryEffect: Inflicts damage equal to the user's level.

name: Aqua Tail
battleEffect: The user attacks by swinging its tail as if it were a vicious wave in a raging storm.
secondaryEffect: No effect.

name: Snatch
battleEffect: The user steals the effects of any attempts to use a healing or stat-changing move.
secondaryEffect: Steals the effects of opponent's next move if it is not a damaging move.

name: Signal Beam
battleEffect: The user attacks with a sinister beam of light. This may also confuse the target.
secondaryEffect: May induce Confusion

name: Genesis Supernova
battleEffect: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Mew, attacks the target with full force. The terrain will be charged with psychic energy.
secondaryEffect: Activates Psychic Terrain

name: Let's Snuggle Forever
battleEffect: After obtaining Z-Power, the user, Mimikyu, punches the target with full force.
secondaryEffect: No effect.

name: Floral Healing
battleEffect: The user restores the target's HP by up to half of its max HP. It restores more HP when the terrain is grass.
secondaryEffect: Heals up to 50% of maximum Hit Points. Heals 100% of maximum Hit Points in Grassy Terrain

name: Ancient Power
battleEffect: The user attacks with a prehistoric power. This may also raise all the user's stats at once.
secondaryEffect: May raise all user's stats one stage.

name: Doom Desire
battleEffect: Two turns after this move is used, a concentrated bundle of light blasts the target.
secondaryEffect: Damage delays 2 turns.

name: High Jump Kick
battleEffect: The target is attacked with a knee kick from a jump. If it misses, the user is hurt instead.
secondaryEffect: If Attack misses, user takes 1/2 max HP of damage.

name: Aromatherapy
battleEffect: The user releases a soothing scent that heals all status conditions affecting the user's party.
secondaryEffect: Heals party's status problems.
zMoveUgradeEffectDetailed: Heals the Hit Points of this Pokémon

name: Soak
battleEffect: The user shoots a torrent of water at the target and changes the target's type to Water.
secondaryEffect: Changes opponent's type to Water-type.

name: Seed Bomb
battleEffect: The user slams a barrage of hard-shelled seeds down on the target from above.
secondaryEffect: No effect.

name: Copycat
battleEffect: The user mimics the move used immediately before it. The move fails if no other move has been used yet.
secondaryEffect: Uses the move used just before it in battle.

name: Twister
battleEffect: The user whips up a vicious tornado to tear at the opposing Pokémon. This may also make them flinch.
secondaryEffect: May cause opponent to flinch. Damage is doubled if opponent is using Fly.

name: Peck
battleEffect: The target is jabbed with a sharply pointed beak or horn.
secondaryEffect: No effect.

name: Aqua Ring
battleEffect: The user envelops itself in a veil made of water. It regains some HP every turn.
secondaryEffect: Recovers 1/16th of user's HP each turn

name: Kinesis
battleEffect: The user distracts the target by bending a spoon. This lowers the target's accuracy.
secondaryEffect: Lowers opponent's Accuracy one stage.

name: Heal Bell
battleEffect: The user makes a soothing bell chime to heal the status conditions of all the party Pokémon.
secondaryEffect: Heals party's status problems.
zMoveUgradeEffectDetailed: Heals the Hit Points of this Pokémon

name: Acrobatics
battleEffect: The user nimbly strikes the target. If the user is not holding an item, this attack inflicts massive damage.
secondaryEffect: Increases damage by 100% if user is not holding an item.

name: Sky Attack
battleEffect: A second-turn attack move where critical hits land more easily. This may also make the target flinch.
secondaryEffect: May cause opponent to flinch.

name: Barrier
battleEffect: The user throws up a sturdy wall that sharply raises its Defense stat.
secondaryEffect: Raises user's Defense two stages.

name: Flower Shield
battleEffect: The user raises the Defense stat of all Grass-type Pokémon in battle with a mysterious power.
secondaryEffect: Raises Defense of Grass-type Pokémon by 1 stage.

name: Spark
battleEffect: The user throws an electrically charged tackle at the target. This may also leave the target with paralysis.
secondaryEffect: May induce paralysis.

name: Razor Wind
battleEffect: In this two-turn attack, blades of wind hit opposing Pokémon on the second turn. Critical hits land more easily.
secondaryEffect: Has an increased Critical Hit ratio

name: Pollen Puff
battleEffect: The user attacks the enemy with a pollen puff that explodes. If the target is an ally, it gives the ally a pollen puff that restores its HP instead.
secondaryEffect: Heals if used on an ally.

name: Light Screen
battleEffect: A wondrous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from special attacks for five turns.
secondaryEffect: Halves Special Attack damage inflicted on the user's side of the field

name: Shadow Force
battleEffect: The user disappears, then strikes the target on the next turn. This move hits even if the target protects itself.
secondaryEffect: The user is protected the first turn, Attacks the second turn. Hits through Protect

name: Solar Beam
battleEffect: In this two-turn attack, the user gathers light, then blasts a bundled beam on the next turn.
secondaryEffect: Charges for the first turn, damages on the second. If Sunny Day is in effect, the charge and attack is in the same turn.

name: Focus Blast
battleEffect: The user heightens its mental focus and unleashes its power. This may also lower the target's  Sp. Def stat.
secondaryEffect: May lower opponent's Special Defense one stage.

name: Electric Terrain
battleEffect: The user electrifies the ground for five turns, powering up Electric-type moves. Pokémon on the ground no longer fall asleep.
secondaryEffect: Activates Electric Terrain for 5 turns

name: Speed Swap
battleEffect: The user exchanges Speed stats with the target.
secondaryEffect: Switches Speed stat with target

name: Mean Look
battleEffect: The user pins the target with a dark, arresting look. The target becomes unable to flee.
secondaryEffect: Prevents the opponent from escaping.

name: Core Enforcer
battleEffect: If the Pokémon the user has inflicted damage on have already used their moves, this move eliminates the effect of the target's Ability.
secondaryEffect: If used after the target Attacks, the target's ability is removed

name: Mega Kick
battleEffect: The target is attacked by a kick launched with muscle-packed power.
secondaryEffect: No effect.

name: Jump Kick
battleEffect: The user jumps up high, then strikes with a kick. If the kick misses, the user hurts itself.
secondaryEffect: If Attack misses, user takes 1/2 max HP of damage.

name: Heal Block
battleEffect: For five turns, the user prevents the opposing team from using any moves, Abilities, or held items that recover HP.
secondaryEffect: Prevents opposing team from using any healing moves, items or abilities for 5 turns

name: Clamp
battleEffect: The target is clamped and squeezed by the user's very thick and sturdy shell for four to five turns.
secondaryEffect: Traps opponent.

name: Bite
battleEffect: The target is bitten with viciously sharp fangs. This may also make the target flinch.
secondaryEffect: May cause opponent to flinch.

name: Steam Eruption
battleEffect: The user immerses the target in superheated steam. This may also leave the target with a burn.
secondaryEffect: May induce burn.

name: Hyperspace Fury
battleEffect: Using its many arms, the user unleashes a barrage of attacks that ignore the effects of moves like Protect and Detect. But the user's Defense stat falls.
secondaryEffect: Hits through Protect

name: Twineedle
battleEffect: The user damages the target twice in succession by jabbing it with two spikes. This may also poison the target.
secondaryEffect: Attacks twice. May induce poison.

name: Dragon Rage
battleEffect: This attack hits the target with a shock wave of pure rage. This attack always inflicts 40 HP damage.
secondaryEffect: Inflicts 40 HP damage.

name: Perish Song
battleEffect: Any Pokémon that hears this song faints in three turns, unless it switches out of battle.
secondaryEffect: All Pokémon on the field faint in 3 turns.

name: Precipice Blades
battleEffect: The user attacks opposing Pokémon by manifesting the power of the land in fearsome blades of stone.
secondaryEffect: No effect.

name: Spirit Shackle
battleEffect: The user attacks while simultaneously stitching the target's shadow to the ground to prevent the target from escaping.
secondaryEffect: Prevents opponent from switching

name: Revelation Dance
battleEffect: The user attacks the target by dancing very hard. The user's type determines the type of this move.
secondaryEffect: Type varies based on form

name: Sunny Day
battleEffect: The user intensifies the sun for five turns, powering up Fire-type moves. It lowers the power of Water-type moves.
secondaryEffect: Causes Sunshine for 5 turns

name: Blue Flare
battleEffect: The user attacks by engulfing the target in an intense, yet beautiful, blue flame. This may also leave the target with a burn.
secondaryEffect: May induce burn.

name: Parting Shot
battleEffect: With a parting threat, the user lowers the target's Attack and Sp. Atk stats. Then it switches with a party Pokémon.
secondaryEffect: Lowers opponent's Attack & Special Attack stats by one stage. Pokémon switches out
zMoveUgradeEffectDetailed: Heals the Hit Points of the Pokémon that switches in after this Pokémon

name: Struggle
battleEffect: This attack is used in desperation only if the user has no PP. It also damages the user a little.
secondaryEffect: Damages user equal to 25% of maximum Hit Points
